 if passed an object that implements the [buffer API](https://docs.python.org/2/c-api/buffer.html), such as the builtin [`memoryview`](https://docs.python.org/2/library/stdtypes.html#memoryview) type.\r\n\r\nNote this a Python 3 flavoured version of #285 from porting that code away from the old `buffer` type.\r\n\r\n```\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  ...\r\n  File \".../osutils.py\", line 753, in pump_string_file\r\n    write(view[offset:offset+segment_size])\r\n  File \".../paramiko/file.py\", line 375, in write\r\n    data = b(data)\r\n  File \".../paramiko/py3compat.py\", line 47, in b\r\n    raise TypeError(\"Expected unicode or bytes, got %r\" % s)\r\nTypeError: Expected unicode or bytes, got <memory at 0x7f0ce4d08510>\r\n```\r\n\r\nParamiko should not care about the types it is passed, provided they are `len`-able and can be written to the underlying (`BytesIO` here) object.","closed_by":{"login":"bitprophet","id":6088,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYwODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6088?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet","html_url":"https://github.com/bitprophet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bitprophet/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/paramiko/paramiko/issues/967/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hoora